nodes.title: Recomendation
widgets_values:
UPDATE! Now u can use 8 sec generation (129 frames, 16 fps) in 1024x576 with res 2m ode and 1280x720 unipc - u get stable result

Use 576p (1024x576) resolution and 81 length and set 16 frame_rate on Video Combine to get the best results
Also u can generate with 121 length and set 24 frame_rate, but u may get more less stable result

Now u can use 720p (1280x720) to generate I2V videos , it will be good in more cases

use CFG 1.0 to get faster generation or use CFG 2.0 to get more cool result, but generation takes more time if cfg>1. With CFG 2.0 u necessarily write negative prompt (cfg 1 doesn't reqiuere negative prompt)

Recomended resolution: 576x1024, 1024x576, 1280x720, 720x1280

How to set length (frames) correctly:

for 16 fps
16 * number of seconds = length and set frame_rate 16 on Video Combine

for 24 fps
24 * number of seconds = length and set frame_rate 24 on Video Combine

I don't recommend generate videos more than 5 seconds because your generation will be unstable and the picture won't be good

I recomend leave 8 steps with 4 steps loras, but u can try set 10 steps - you may get better result

Try adjusting WanVideoBlockSwap settings

My results with rtx 5080 generation

With 4steps loras
576p, light Lora 250928, 81 length (16 fps), 10 steps, unipc, cfg 2.0 (high noise only) ≈ 5-6 minutes
720p, light Lora 250928, 81 length (16 fps), 10 steps, unipc, cfg 2.0 (high noise only) ≈ 10-11 minutes
576p, light Lora 250928, 129 length (16 fps), 10 steps, unipc, cfg 2.0 (high noise only) ≈ 8 minutes
720p, light Lora 250928, 129 length (16 fps), 10 steps, unipc, cfg 2.0 (high noise only) ≈ 15-16 minutes

Without LightX
480p, 81 length (16 fps), 20 steps, unipc, cfg 3.5 ≈ 10 minutes
720p, 81 length (16 fps), 30 steps, unipc, cfg 3.5 ≈ 30-32 minutes

Models and .whl files
widgets_values:
Required models for WAN 2.2 I2V Workflow:

WAN 2.2 I2V Models:  https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy_fp8_scaled/tree/main/I2V
Lightning Lora 4steps: https://huggingface.co/lightx2v/Wan2.2-Lightning/tree/main/Wan2.2-T2V-A14B-4steps-lora-250928 (i recomend rename files while you're downloading them)
Text Encoder: https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/Wan_2.1_ComfyUI_repackaged/blob/main/split_files/text_encoders/umt5_xxl_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled.safetensors
VAE: https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/Wan_2.1_ComfyUI_repackaged/blob/main/split_files/vae/wan_2.1_vae.safetensors

(Optional) NSFW WAN 2.2 Lora - https://civitai.com/models/1307155?modelVersionId=2073605 and https://civitai.com/models/1811313/wan-dr34ml4y-all-in-one-nsfw

If you need GGUF Version - https://huggingface.co/QuantStack/Wan2.2-I2V-A14B-GGUF/tree/main
I recomend use lightx lora instead 4 steps high and low noise lora for GGUF models and set strength 1 - https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/blob/main/Lightx2v/lightx2v_T2V_14B_cfg_step_distill_v2_lora_rank256_bf16.safetensors
Only UNIPC Sampler


File save location

ComfyUI/
├───📂 models/
│   ├───📂 diffusion_models/
│   │   ├─── Wan2_2-I2V-A14B_HIGH_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled_KJ.safetensors
│   │   └─── Wan2_2-I2V-A14B-LOW_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled_KJ.safetensors
│   ├───📂 loras/
│   │   ├───high_noise_model.safetensors
│   │   ├───low_noise_model.safetensors
│   ├───📂 text_encoders/
│   │   └─── umt5_xxl_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled.safetensors 
│   └───📂 vae/
│       └── wan_2.1_vae.safetensors


SageAttention.whl - https://github.com/woct0rdho/SageAttention/releases/tag/v2.2.0-windows. To install sageattention, u can .whl change to .zip and:
1. If u don't have sageattention, just put folders from .zip to ComfyUI\python_embeded\Lib\site-packages
2. If u have older version sageattention, delete folders with sageattention in ComfyUI\python_embeded\Lib\site-packages and put new folders from .zip

To install Triton (if u don't have Triton) go to ComfyUI\python_embeded and install by command [pip install triton] via cmd

if you got error BaseLoaderKJ._patch_modules.<locals>.attention_sage() got an unexpected keyword argument 'transformer_options', use run_nvidia_gpu - sageattention.bat instead run_nvidia_gpu.bat in ComfyUI from .zip archive
